es and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When David Haliburton was born about 1126, in Berwickshire, Scotland, his father, Truite Haliburton, was 33 and his mother, Janet Seton, was 28. He married Margarete Cameron about 1159, in Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died before 1207."},"et":{"about 1126–Bef 1207":"umbes 1126–enne 1207","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1126–1207":"1126–1207","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1152–Male":"1152–Surnud","1160–1207":"1160–1207","–Male":"Surnud","1095–1150":"1095–1150","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1176":"1176","1220":"1220","1152":"1152","1130":"1130","1151":"1151","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Bef 1207":"enne 1207","Abt 1152":"umbes 1152","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1100":"1100","about 1126":"umbes 1126","about 1159":"umbes 1159","1207":"1207","Haliburton, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dirleton Castle, East Lothian, Scotland":"Dirleton, East Lothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Haliburton, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1126–Bef 1207":"noin 1126–ennen vuotta 1207","1125–Male":"1125–Kuollut","1126–1207":"1126–1207","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1152–Male":"1152–Kuollut","1160–1207":"1160–1207","–Male":"Kuollut","1095–1150":"1095–1150","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut